latestPosts.alt: Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of ‎2 people, henna, wedding and ‎text that says '‎How to Plan a Rainy Season Wedding Without a Breakdown ققم ত‎'‎‎.

childPosts.alt: Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of ‎2 people, henna, wedding and ‎text that says '‎How to Plan a Rainy Season Wedding Without a Breakdown ققم ত‎'‎‎.

Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'VENUE TIPS Choose your venue wisely: Prefer indoor or semi- semi-covered venues If outdoors, go for pukka flooring (avoid grass/mud) /mud) the site Ask about rainwater drainage at Always have α Plan B covered space (banquet, hall, tent) Keep waterproof tents or canopies ready for baraat + guests'.

Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'DÉCOR TIPS Rain-friendly wedding décor hacks: hacks: Use artificial flowers or dried florals- real ones wilt quickly Stick to open areas minima ceiling décor in Choose plastic-laminated signage or acrylic boards Place non-slip mats at guest entry points Avoid paper props or pampas grass- -they get soggy fast'.

Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'MAKEUP TIPS Waterproof & monsoon-proof bridal makeup: Use matte, waterproof foundation (no dewy dewy base!) Gel-based eyeliner, waterproof mascara & long long-wear ipstick are musts Cream blush > powder blush (less cakey in humidity) Set everything with a strong setting spray Keep blotting sheets in your emergency kit'.

Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'MEHENDI TIPS Rain + mehendi = disaster if not careful: Choose indoor, airy space for application Avoid direct fans or humid corners Use a lemon-sugar spray to seal design after drying Keep cotton cloth instead of tissues for patting Do NOT NOT wash hands for 12 hours, especially in humidity'.

Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of hair product and text that says 'HAIR & FRIZZ CONTROL Frizz-free bridal hair, even in humidity: Use anti-frizz serum before styling Avoid open hairstyles in outdoor setups Hair updos (buns, braids) last onger in moisture Lock everything with α humidity- resistant hairspray Keep a small anti-frizz touch-up cream in your clutch'.

Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'GUEST COMFORT IDEAS Your guests will thank you: Provide umbrellas or raincoats for outdoor setups entry Place welcome towel stations at Serve hot drinks: chai, kahwa, kahwa coffee to keep everyone warm Bug sprays or mosquito roll-ons on tables Place clear signboards with directions (rainproofed!)'.

Photo by WeddingBazaar on June 05, 2025. May be an image of wedding and text that says 'WEDDING SHOOT IN THE RAIN? YES PLEASE! Monsoon = Magical wedding content: Use transparent umbrellas as props Shoot in covered terraces, porches, vintage windows Wear light pastels or jewel tones -they pop in cloudy skies Carry towels & touch-up kits Capture chai-pakoda & rain dance moments'.

latestPosts.caption:
Congratulations to @realhinakhan @rockyj1 on their holy matrimony! ✨🧿❤️

For her nuptials, the radiant Hina Khan @realhinakhan chose our handloom saree in opal green, with gold and silver threads tracing age-old motifs across its weave. A light blush border, embroidered with threadwork and zardozi, framed the drape with quiet intricacy.
Subtle pleated gota detailing added depth to the fabric, while a soft pink veil with a scalloped hem lent a dreamlike finish. On her #MMsaree, her name and her husband’s were delicately embroidered- a personal note stitched into tradition. The look was complemented by imperial heirlooms from @manishmalhotrajewellery.
Alongside, her husband @rockyj1 wore our signature kurta in ecru- understated, timeless, and tailored to the moment.
